item.description:
@usernamelol wrote:

[quote=“Ron, post:30, topic:120816”][quote author=ß Boring ß link=topic=170390.msg1578290#msg1578290 date=1183877510]
Thanks Casey and Flair - Though, what’s so great about firefox? and whats wrong with IE?
Tell me the differences -.-

EDIT - Yes! I’m using it right now. It’s way better than ie …
[/quote]
Hey if you really wanna have some fun with firefox, download this extension to get rid of all the ads you see.

addons.mozilla.org

Adblock Plus – Get this Extension for 🦊 Firefox (en-US)

Download Adblock Plus for Firefox. Blocks annoying video ads on YouTube, Facebook ads, banners and much more. Adblock Plus blocks all annoying ads, and supports websites by not blocking unobtrusive ads by default (configurable).

Click on install, it will prompt you so wait 5 seconds, and hit install. Installs really quick. It will prompt you to restart Firefox (don’t worry when it restarts, all the pages you have open will be reopened), and it will prompt you (yes again) to pick a list to block. Pick the 1st list, and you will never see ads again. AdBlock Plus is the best!

And… how did people know I hide my online status? Yea… sometimes I get really dumb PMs and I just want to be left alone. I switch it on and off though. :)[/quote]
sucks when you want to click your own ads (on different ip)
